snippet.textDisplay:
Disney's newest lands, Star wars and Pandora, Both were pretty epically done, but the rides sucked.
The river ride? it is a visual masterpiece, but ultimately has zero re-ride value.
Flight of passage? its okay, i mean your pretty much watching a movie... on a stand that moves a little bit... no thrill, very little re-ride value.
Millenium falcon? I've played better VR games. just buy 2 joysticks and go play star citizen if you wanna do it at home.
(newest star wars ride i haven't personally done yet, but ive seen the videos of it, seems fun but ehh.)
and the food at both these lands SUCKED!
and the droid/lightsaber/bird-dragon thing are cool, but not 100 bucks cool. besides T-shirts and hats, nothing really... cool to buy.
Night time again, both look amazing, but its just a walkthrough.

Toy story land on the other hand I think Disney hit a masterpiece, its fun, inviting, the slinky dog coaster + bumper cars + toy story mania, also its super cool in day-time or night time.
Food is Meh (good but not anything amazing) and merch is Meh.

The thing universal needs to focus on, is make the lands interactable like how the HP area's are with the wands,
Dont just make the areas visually pleasing, but make them fun to stay in, easter eggs, Hidden story plots about the areas,
Things to hunt for/interact with. it doesn't always have to be a ride.
Like how in HP worlds you have all those stores bursting with cool and funny merchandise from the HP world, make the new lands like the HP lands and I won't ever even bother with Disney again.
